txt.en: Collect stone-rubbings from the tombs of Aufaltor ([placeholder]/[placeholder])

You have discovered many ancient, crumbling tombs within Aufaltor.

If Thuringwath was once a land inhabited by peoples other than servants of the Enemy, perhaps collecting stone-rubbings from the tombs might shed light on this lost history of Middle-earth.

You should collect stone-rubbings from the tombs of Aufaltor.

You have collected many stone-rubbings from the tombs at Aufaltor.
Many are the tombs of Aufaltor, and many are the Dead that guard them.
Collect stone-rubbings from the tombs of Aufaltor
You are unable to discern the lineages of those entombed at Aufaltor, but you store the stone-rubbings away that you might bring them to the archives of Minas Tirith.
Tombs can be found throughout Aufaltor in Thuringwath.

Tombs can be found throughout Aufaltor in Thuringwath.\n\nFading inscriptions on the ancient tombs of Aufaltor might be preserved through stone-rubbings. You should take stone-rubbings of the tombs of Aufaltor.
